('prt_f562568ec001eRVgUHLb37NnUj', 'msg_f5625646b0011Wa2BiGZK1NdmP', 'ses_0a9dac278ffeGqD1mzTDArbRM0', 1783856720108, 1783856729771, '{"type":"reasoning","text":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me analyze the differences between the user''s conversation-backup skill and the three referenced issues.\n\n1. **#27752 - opencode-mempalace-persistence**: A plugin that auto-saves conversations to a local vector database (MemPalace) in real-time. Features: auto-sync every turn, categorization, knowledge graph extraction, async mining. Uses plugin hooks (chat.message, event:session.idle).\n\n2. **#19017 - Save conversation history locally**: A simple feature request asking for local file-based conversation saves. Very basic request, no implementation details.\n\n3. **#9387 - opencode session export to markdown or json**: A feature request for a CLI command to export sessions to markdown or JSON format. Has a PR (#32262) associated. Single-session export, one-way (export only), file-based output.\n\nNow let me compare these with the user''s conversation-backup skill:\n\n**User''s conversation-backup skill:**\n- Exports to SQL format (complete database dump, not just text)\n- Bidirectional: export AND import (cross-device migration)\n- Uses git for version control and sync (conversations-backup branch)\n- Path/project-agnostic with placeholder substitution ({{WORKTREE}}, {{PROJECT_ID}})\n- Cross-device via git remote URL identification\n- Project-scoped (per-project conversations)\n- Uses INSERT OR REPLACE for safe merging\n- Dry-run preview before import\n- Safety: new-session check, excludes current session from export\n- No external dependencies (Node.js 22+ built-in sqlite)\n- Operates on dedicated git branch to avoid polluting work branch\n\nKey differentiators:\n1. **vs #27752 (MemPalace)**: MemPalace is a vector DB for semantic search/retrieval - it''s about making conversations searchable and usable by AI. The user''s skill is about exact-fidelity backup and cross-device migration. Different use cases entirely.\n2. **vs #19017**: That''s just a wish for local saves - the user''s skill is a complete implementation with git-based sync.\n3. **vs #9387**: Export to markdown/json is one-way, single-session, human-readable format. The user''s skill does full SQL database dump (all tables), bidirectional (export+import), multi-session, and is designed for cross-device migration rather than human reading.\n\nLet me summarize the key differences and advantages.\n","time":{"start":1783856720108,"end":1783856729770}}'),
('prt_f56258eac0019AmmgS4IeGF8ye', 'msg_f5625646b0011Wa2BiGZK1NdmP', 'ses_0a9dac278ffeGqD1mzTDArbRM0', 1783856729772, 1783856741326, '{"type":"text","text":"以下是你的 conversation-backup skill 与三个竞品的对比分析：\n\n---\n\n## 对比总结\n\n| 维度 | 你的 skill | #27752 MemPalace | #19017 本地保存 | #9387 导出 md/json |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **核心定位** | 跨设备对话迁移 | 向量数据库语义检索 | 纯诉求，无实现 | 单会话只读导出 |\n| **方向** | 双向（导出+导入） | 单向（写入向量库） | 未定义 | 单向（仅导出） |\n| **格式** | SQL 完整数据库转储 | 向量嵌入 | 未定义 | Markdown/JSON 文本 |\n| **同步方式** | Git 版本控制 | 本地实时同步 | 未定义 | 手动 CLI 命令 |\n| **跨设备** | 原生支持（git remote 识别） | 不支持 | 不支持 | 不支持 |\n| **数据完整性** | 全表级（sessions/messages 等所有表） | 仅提取的知识图谱事实 | 未定义 | 单会话文本 |\n| **路径适配** | 占位符自动替换（{{WORKTREE}}） | 无此需求 | 未定义 | 无此需求 |\n| **安全性** | 新会话检查、排除当前会话、dry-run 预览、独立分支 | 无 | 无 | 无 |\n\n---\n\n## 你的核心差异化优势\n\n1. **唯一解决跨设备迁移问题** — 其他三个都是单设备场景，你的 skill 是唯一通过 git 实现多设备间对话完整迁移的方案\n\n2. **全量数据库级备份 vs 文本/向量级** — SQL 导出保留了完整的数据库结构和关系，导入后可直接恢复使用，而非仅用于人类阅读（md/json）或语义搜索（向量库）\n\n3. **双向闭环** — 导出+导入+dry-run 预览+确认机制，形成完整的备份恢复工作流，其他方案都是单向的\n\n4. **零依赖** — 利用 Node.js 22+ 内置 `node:sqlite`，无需 npm install，无外部服务依赖（MemPalace 需要额外的向量数据库）\n\n5. **Git 原生集成** — 对话备份跟随代码仓库一起版本管理，自带变更历史和协作能力，独立分支不污染工作区\n\n---\n\n## 建议回复维护者的差异化说明\n\n你可以这样回复：\n\n> Unlike #27752 (vector DB for semantic search), #19017 (local save wish), and #9387 (single-session text export), this skill solves a distinct problem: **cross-device conversation migration** with full database fidelity. It provides bidirectional SQL export/import via git, with path-agnostic placeholder substitution, dry-run preview, and zero external dependencies. The existing issues focus on single-device persistence or human-readable export — none address moving complete conversation state between machines.","time":{"start":1783856729772,"end":1783856741325}}'),
