('prt_f560d1993001v3DIETZnq0htTG', 'msg_f560d1661001f9n0QiNxAWjQda', 'ses_0a9fbb56effeQaZdXvhiM6xltc', 1783855126931, 1783855130222, '{"type":"reasoning","text":"Now I need to commit and push these files. But the user didn''t explicitly ask me to commit. Let me re-read the instructions - \"NEVER commit changes unless the user explicitly asks you to.\" The user said \"推送到git\" earlier which was about the initial push. Now they asked to add README files. They didn''t explicitly ask to commit and push these READMEs. But in context, they''re preparing to open source this, so they likely want these committed too. Let me ask.\n\nActually, looking at the context again - the user is preparing to open source this project. They asked to add READMEs. It''s very likely they want these committed and pushed. But the rule says \"NEVER commit changes unless the user explicitly asks you to.\" I should just create the files and let the user know, they can ask to commit if they want.\n","time":{"start":1783855126931,"end":1783855130221}}'),
